=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Tutorials_08-Scoping-and-Plotting_ex6 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: sustained
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -14.8272
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5007
  pitch_clarity: 122.0417
  inharmonicity: 0.0014
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -5.0630
  resonance_freq: 430.6641

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: 08. Scoping and Plotting Example 6
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Tutorials/Getting-Started/08-Scoping-and-Plotting.html
// Tags: 08-Scoping-and-Plotting, Tutorials
// ---
// --- Example 6 ---
{ [SinOsc.ar(440, 0, 0.2), SinOsc.ar(442, 0, 0.2)] }.play;
s.play;
